  "texts": [
    "We propose a standardized, interpretable prompt structure that incorporates step-by-step, rule-based reasoning to support consistent evaluation across various experimental configurations.",
    "The benchmark spans five settings: i) zero-shot prompting, ii) few-shot prompting with labeled exemplars, iii) in-context learning (ICL) with extended examples, iv) supervised fine-tuning using parameter-efficient low rank adaptation (LoRA), and v) a hybrid approach that combines LLM reasoning with traditional deep learning (DL) detector.",
    "The main contributions of this work are as follows: To the best of our knowledge, this study is the first to investigate the application of LLMs for numeric AD in power systems.",
    "Our work bridges the gap between LLM reasoning and structured measurements.",
    " A comprehensive evaluation framework is developed, consisting of i) multiple prompt-engineering strategies for zero-shot, few-shot, and ICL, ii) parameter-efficient fine-tuning using LoRA, and iii) a hybrid configuration that integrates LLM-driven feature selection with a standard deep-learning AD approach."
